5|$|Creationists {{argue against}} {{evolution}} <b>on</b> <b>the</b> <b>grounds</b> <b>that</b> <b>it</b> cannot explain certain non-evolutionary processes, such as abiogenesis, the Big Bang, or {{the meaning of}} life. In such instances, evolution is being redefined {{to refer to the}} entire history of the universe, and it is argued that if one aspect of the universe is seemingly inexplicable, the entire body of scientific theories must be baseless. At this point, objections leave the arena of evolutionary biology and become general scientific or philosophical disputes.|$|E
